hopobject.body: Could I borrow your phone, please? prinivil webmd The regulator calls for a minimum wage clause to be inserted into contracts between private firms that provide elderly care and councils which pay for it. "We believe that not only should contracts commissioning home care include a requirement that care workers are paid at least the national minimum wage, including payment for travel time, but also that local authorities should be transparent and set out how the rates they pay cover these costs."
